==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Didelphys
<hw>Di*del"phys</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Didelphia</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Formerly, any
marsupial; but the term is now restricted to an American genus which
includes the opossums, of which there are many species. See
<er>Opossum</er>. <altsp>[Written also <asp>Didelphis</asp>.]</altsp>
See <xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>
<rj><au>Cuvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Didine</ent>⟦br⟧
